# Token Bucket API {#token-bucket .reference}

{~ TODO: add an example for distributed refill coordination ~}

The :abbr[API]{title="Application Programming Interface"} refill model uses :math[r \times t] tokens over time, where `r` is the refill rate.[^rate]

::math
tokens(t) = \min(capacity, tokens_0 + r t)
::

For more background, see :cite[Tanenbaum, Computer Networks] on token bucket algorithms.

## Rust Client

Press :kbd[Ctrl+Shift+B] to build the project, or :kbd[F5] to run with the debugger attached.

```rust
pub fn allow(tokens: u32, requested: u32) -> bool {
    tokens >= requested
}
```
{.line-numbers highlight=3}

| Field | Required | Example |
| :--- | :---: | ---: |
| capacity | yes | 120 |
| refill_per_sec | yes | 10 |
| burst | no | 240 |

Capacity
: The maximum number of tokens the bucket can hold.

Burst
: A temporary allowance above the steady-state :abbr[QoS]{title="Quality of Service"} request rate.

[^rate]: Production systems usually derive `r` from a per-second throughput budget.
